Madam is the panorama bar and restaurant on the 20th floor of the newly developed @adam_toren. It is the square part, just beneath the observation desk (HELLO IM ADAM) and above the 19th floor revolving restaurant where they will serve 5- and 8-course dinners. Madam has a more brasserie style menu with classics like steak tartar, Caesar salad and rack of lamb.  Going up in a spectacular elevator and welcomed with a glass of Champagne, we were first overtaken by the VIEW! Words can't describe it properly, but maybe you can stay tuned on @amsterdamview and see for yourself.  Our sneak peak 4 course dinner started with smoked salmon followed by tom kha kai, supreme chicken and yes: there was still some room for a chocolate mousse. We loved it. Service and food are only in need of some fine tuning, but all is done from the heart.  We are curious what Moon is going to be like! AMSTERDAM • There are macaroons, and then there are kokosmakronen - coconut macaroons! We tried some amazing ones found at Noodermarkt.  From @thedutchtable: Dutch have an incredible cookie culture. Grocery stores stock shelves of the most amazing combinations, shapes, ingredients and flavors. Coconut macaroons, or kokosmakronen, are found in a variety of shapes and sizes. Some are small and high, others piped in a circle and flat. Some are yellow (depending on whether you include the egg yolk), others plain white, but the flavor and texture is always moist, coconutty and sweet. Kokosmakronen are usually baked on circles of edible potato starch paper.

We have a Fish and Chips revival in Amsterdam. Viscafé De Gouden Hoek, close to the Westerpark, was the first offering mainly Fish and Chips from daily catches. We love the ambiance which is very stylish and strengthening the concept. Here is what they do menu wise: some classic startes like croquettes, oysters and crab, but the main focus is of course on fish and chips. You choose one of the daily catches and combine it with one of three crusts with accompanying sauce. Choose from the classic crust with remoulade, a panko-crust with piccalilli or tempura-crust with Japanese Sriracha. When you don’t have enough at hand, daily catches ask for good communication between kitchen and service staff. Which in our case didn't go very well. We were surprised when two out of three dishes served had a totally different fish then the one we had ordered. And we had to find out ourselves. Ah what the heck, the taste was good. Service wasn’t to stable though. Some get it, others don’t. Do we recommend this place? Yup! We like the concept, we love the taste, maybe they can improve service a little. ——— Food ⭐️⭐️️⭐️⭐️ Service ⭐️⭐️⭐️ Ambiance ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ ——— Viscafé De Gouden Hoek Van Limburg Stirumstraat 10A  020-2299009, reservations advised www.degoudenhoek.nl  Open: Tue-Fri 17.00-0.00, Sat-Sun 16.00-0.00 ——— #dinner #fishandchips #westerpark #staatsliedenbuurt #amsterdamwest #amsterdam #amsterdamrestaurants #amsterdamfood #food #proefwerk #instafood #foodstagram #restaurantreview #amsterdamreview ——— Follow AMSTERDAM RESTAURANTS for more reviews of your next to know favorites.  Tag the friend that you want to bring here.

Classic and perfectly served. Bread came after we asked for some pieces. 30 min wait in line for Best Thai in town. 👌  THAI BIRD RESTAURANT  An elegant restaurant with more than 100 seats, Thai Bird serves tasty dishes to a crowd of hungry diners nightly. Although the restaurant is large, there seems to be a line out the door most evenings. The wait is never very long however, and soon you will be seated with a Singha in hand (did you know it is pronounced “Sing” and not “Sing-ha”?). Begin your meal by sharing an order of loempia or saté, tom yum soup, or perhaps Northern Thai lobster meatballs. The menu has something for everyone, with seafood, chicken, noodle, beef and vegetarian dishes. Most main courses run from €15-18 each and come with steamed rice. Service is quick and friendly.  #amsterdamfood #amsterdam #thai #redcurry #instafood #delicious

"Geef mij maar Amsterdam, dat is mooier dan Parijs" - Johnny Jordaan  The Jordaan - traditional home of the dramatic vibrato that is Jordaanlied music and current home of Amsterdam's “most beautiful canal," De Brouwersgracht. A wobbly grid of quiet, narrow streets, the Jordaan is as much Amsterdam heritage as wooden shoes & rain.  On Rozengracht, along the bottom edge of the Jordaan, you'll find Salmuera (@sal_amsterdam) w/ an exceptional mix of cocktails & ceviche. Further down, the terrace at Brandstof (@barbrandstof) is the perfect place to observe one of the great spectacles of Amsterdam – the convergence of pedestrian, bike, scooter, car, taxi, bus, & tram. Who will win?? (SPOILER – It's usually the tram.) Heading north off Rozengracht leads into the Jordaan & over some of the city's prettiest canals. If you get nice light & want to win Instagram, Egelantiersgracht (#egelantiersgracht) & Bloemgracht (#bloemgracht) are great options.  Saturday mornings on Westerstraat, you can either have beers & cigarettes with the locals at De Blaffende Vis (#blaffendevis) or head to the organic market at the Noorderkerk (#noorderkerkmarket). If looking for dinner, De Reiger (#dereiger) has maybe the best ribs in Amsterdam & definitely the coolest restaurant cat. Daalder (#daalder), in a former jazz bar on Lindengracht, also has great food, but unconfirmed if there’s a restaurant cat.  After dinner (or anytime really), the Jordaan has a solid supply of brown bars. Cafe Thijsen (@cafe_thijssen) & De Tuin (#cafedetuin) are usually fun. But if you're looking for a truly “cultural” experience, the fluorescent pink, late-night beacon of Cafe Nol (@cafenolamsterdam) will definitely blow up anything you have to do the next morning. There's a burger under that egg! Amsterdam had THE BEST food and I'm a picky eater (getting better). I was walking to another place and passed this restaurant on my way and came back another day. I was sick coming from Iceland and had a wicked sore throat my first couple of days in Amsterdam. I got this delicious and huge burger with equally delicious and fresh fries. Every thing was seasoned and so so good. They had a tea which soothed my throat almost instantaneously as well with lemon ginger and honey. I left stuffed and took home a slice of chocolate pie which was also amazing. The decor of this place was super cute and service was great.
